<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-0539 </DOCNO><TEXT>The major part of Hazards in the Chemical Laboratory is an alphabeticalguide to hazardous chemicals and measures to be taken if accidents occurduring their use. This edition reflects the developments in the Healthand Safety at Work Act, 1974, and its effect upon laboratory managementwith regard to the implementation of the act. The role of managementin enforcing health and safety regulations is emphasised. Dangers fromfire and explosions, reactive chemicals, toxic substances, cleaning andremoving spillages and the general environmental aspects such as heatingand ventilation are considered. Detailed guidance in the use of radioactivesubstances and the hazards of ionising and non-ionizing radiations arediscussed. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>